      "date": "2017-09-30 18:43:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI don't understand the need for this patch. I can see from your report that the test is failing, but what part of the path is missing that would need \"-p\"? The error reported in the ticket is:\n\n  mkdir -i2 -c2 /mnt/lustre/d102d.sanity failed\n\nWhat part of that path is missing that -p is needed?\n\nSeparately, it would be good to fix the problem of tar not running on RHEL 7.",
